Hon. Emmanuel Jekada, Chairman, All Progressive Congress, Kaduna Chapter has stated that he has neither made nor submitted any list of appointees to the Kaduna state Governor Mal. Nasir El-Rufai for appointment. Jekada made the refutation in a swift reaction to media report that he earlier submitted names of three candidates for appointment by el-Rufai but was rejected. He said the information was the handi work of mischief makers who did not mean well with the cordial relationship existing between him and the governor. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! The chairman stated in phone chat that he has no problem with his governor Mal. El-Rufai therefore has no reason to have fallen apart with him over any appointments or otherwise as claimed and published in some Social Media. He said the earlier report that he, “The retired Airforce General, Air Commodore Emmanuel Jekada’s exit days in office with the party are numbered as a result of the impasse,,”was full blown blatant lies by his enemies. SGF Attributes Jettisoning Of Values, Culture To Cause Of Economic, Political Disarray In Africa Ibori Already A Successful Businessman Before Becoming Delta Governor- ODU “It’s a lie that, I Jekada who hails from Zango Kataf in Southern Kaduna area of the State, is said to have been having grudges with the Governor over political appointees”, he said. “It was a lie that I presented names of three persons to Governor El-Rufai as lists of candidates for political appointment.”